                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yesterday I grouped for the first time in the zone, Wall of Slaughter, a zone I had not previously visited (as I had only bought OoW that day, and that was only at the request of my guildmates, who wanted me to come with them to hunt there.)  I got the group by virtue of the time - 4AM, and zero, that is zero enchanters LFG until I decided to try an LDoN adventure, got a tell, and off I went.
<br />

<br />
My group was top-notch: I suspect that at least a couple of them were hard core, time-geared raiding types, who were slumming at that point.  
<br />

<br />
On the one hand, I did have a good time in WoS.  I don't know how much I contributed to the group, and am not sure I made a good impression, something that always bothers me (sigh.)
<br />

<br />
I discovered, to my surprise, that I could mez adds on the yard trash with my highest level mez spell, which is Sleep at this point.   Unless, of course, I got a resist.
<br />

<br />
It has been many, many, many levels since I died that fast.
<br />

<br />
With Arcane Rune, I am lasting - I think - one and a half rounds before death.  If I cast Sleep under the assumption that it will be resisted, and then immediately cast Word of Morrell, I could, on occasion, get all the way through the spell and try to re-mez.  However, on most pulls, <span style="font-style: italic">I am dying before the casting time of my spells has completed.</span>  I am not sure what the casting time of Word of Morrell is, but I recall it being relatively low.  
<br />

<br />
The cleric had an epic, so I spent most of the evening mezzing with 10-15% mana, operating on the C1 that I can clicky-cast with a pair of pants that I got a long time ago.  Poor cleric!  On one occasion (when I happened to die while I was looting my bod, and thus had not been able to cast Arcane Rune..)  "Um, was that one round?"  Talk about flashback time, ha ha ha!  Yes, poor, longsuffering Cleric, that was one round.  I think it might have been a complete round... though maybe not.
<br />

<br />
At any rate, I think I should try to upgrade some gear and get more HP (I can push 3900 HP, if I am buffed until I glow.)  Because of my schedule and playstyle, trying to get LDoN equipment is probably my best bet.  Anyone have suggestions on LDoN equipment I could wear that would be suitable to venture into OoW?
<br />

<br />
As always, thank you for your help!
<br />

<br />
Jen <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Edit:
<br />

<br />
I should add here that I do not do much raiding, and I have exactly two flags in PoP: one is the PoJ flag to get into Valor and Storms (right before they unlocked the zones of course) and the other is from the hedge-maze thing in Plane of Nightmare.  I am open to suggestions on other types of gear, but to be of any use to me, it must be obtainable by a casual, 6-man group of players.
<br />

<br />
Jen <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
