                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ornate Silk pants would be nice if you can catch that spawn.   Upgrade from clicky clarity to clicky Tranquility, though the stats on ornate really aren't much better than Skyshrine armor.
<br />

<br />
Look into LDoN equipment.  Those are one grouppable and your charm updates over time to give you more stats.
<br />

<br />
Try GoD Sewer trials.  Some okay stuff drops from named and raadom mobs in those. 
<br />

<br />
Complete the backdoor flags for more stats on your charm.
<br />
Torment, Tactics, HoH and CoD all have one groupable backdoor flags.
<br />

<br />
Also, I suggest looking at the Magelos of other people here who profess to be in casual guilds for ideas.  (I am not, so don't use mine as an example.)
<br />

<br />
If you are willing to spend about $20, I think, get an Everquest premium membership and do advanced searches for each slot.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=554032" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sunaeri LaSuin</a>
<br />

<br />
The strength of the enchanter is in the strength of their group. 
<br />
The weakness of the enchanter is in the strength of the mobs assaulting their group. 
<br />

<br />
The strength of mobs have outgrown the strength of groups, so enchanters are weak.
<br />
_________________
<br />

<br />
Two ways to help make in camp crowd control survivable:
<br />
Reduce heal aggro 
<br />
Remove component from rune line</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
