                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You might also look into Earthweave gear.  Yes, this is tradeskilled from Elemental drops . . . but available in bazaar and the stats 70-100ish hp are pretty equivelent to what is dropping in OOW lately so prices have dropped very much.  Earthweave is heavy on the hp and light on the mana.  Items which used to go for 45 kp on Xev have dropped down to about 20 kp.
<br />

<br />
Other suggestions for WoS survival . . .
<br />

<br />
Yes level up and also max every damage mitigation AA you can buy.
<br />

<br />
At level 65 I quadriple rune myself:  have ER 3 ready for a real emergency, Arcane Rune always, Rune of Zeb as well and then uproar to keep the Rune of Zeb safe and protect my peridot investment. I also keep an animation pet up (think of it as another rune) and give it an uproar and Virtue if the cleric is in a friendly mood.  I beg every hp buff I can beg, borrow or steal:  Pot9, Symbol, Vie, Boar, Brells, Fo7.  Greater Wolf form can give you the speed to kite ahead of those fast-moving mobs.  Tribute can give you another 150 hp and other buffs.
<br />

<br />
And if your mez is resisted start kiting your mob around.  Your pet can divert it long enough to get off a WoM or a root (casts fast) or even a mez.  Buy the Jagged Gravestone of Affliction (Extended Torment IV) augment in LDoN which will extend all these spells duration a bit.
<br />

<br />
This won't work in a pickup group, but my buddies have learned to notice when I'm in trouble and snap off a root or a stun that gives me the leeway for a second cast of mez and a real lockdown.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
