                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My magelo is a pretty good example of what a non-raiding enchanter can do if you throw plat at the problem.  
<br />

<br />
I actually was in WoS for the first time with my chanter the other day (I don't play her much anymore) with an uberguild friend of mine who wanted to show me the place and finally get me dinged 66.  I kept AR and Rune of Zeb on myself at all times, and managed to survive a couple short bursts of aggro, which was a pleasant surprise.  Had a bard doing the pulling and at least half of the CC though, so most of my time was spent trying to find ways to NOT be FM all the time.  At least half of the folks in the group were drunk though, so the conversation was interesting.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=319493" target="_blank" class="postlink">Vihanna</a>
<br />
Xegony</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
